title: Keralan Style Cod Loin En-papillote With Crisp Citrus Keralan Slaw
summary: Keralan Style Cod Loin En-papillote With Crisp Citrus Keralan Slaw is a gluten free, dairy free, and pescatarian main course. This recipe makes 3 servings with 392 calories, 29g of protein, and 21g of fat each. For $4.05 per serving, this recipe covers 41% of your daily requirements of vitamins and minerals. 1 person were glad they tried this recipe. If you have lime zest, turmeric, bean shoots, and a few other ingredients on hand, you can make it. To use up the honey you could follow this main course with the Honey Gingerbread as a dessert. It will be a hit at your The Fourth Of July event. From preparation to the plate, this recipe takes approximately 14 minutes. With a spoonacular score of 90%, this dish is tremendous. Try Keralan vegetable curry, Crunchy Keralan Salad, and Keralan Salad Recipe for similar recipes.

winePairing.pairingText: Cod works really well with Pinot Grigio, Gruener Veltliner, and Pinot Noir. Fish is as diverse as wine, so it's hard to pick wines that go with every fish. A crisp white wine, such as a pinot grigio or Grüner Veltliner, will suit any delicately flavored white fish. Meaty, strongly flavored fish such as salmon and tuna can even handle a light red wine, such as a pinot noir. The Tiamo Pinot Grigio with a 4.4 out of 5 star rating seems like a good match. It costs about 11 dollars per bottle.

productMatches.title: Tiamo Pinot Grigio
productMatches.description: Light straw yellow color. Fresh and rich fruity aromas of apple and pear with a hint of citrus fruit that fade into the floral bouquet. Fresh and fruity, very clean and crisp.Tiamo Pinot Grigio pairs well with a wide array of lighter cuisine, especially fish/shellfish, poultry, pastas in cream sauce and softer cheeses. It's also an ideal aperitif.
